Short:        Tidies icons, adds preview icons
Author:       Kerry Thompson
Uploader:     kwezza@gmail.com
Type:         util/wb
Version:      2.0
Architecture: m68k-amigaos >= 3.2.0
Distribution: Aminet
Requires:     AmigaOS 3.2+; lha (for backups)

Workbench drawers have a way of drifting into chaos over time,
especially after large extractions, cover disks, or years of
"I will sort it later" installs.

iTidy is a utility for tidying icon layouts and drawer windows in
a consistent, repeatable way. It can process a single folder or
work recursively through subfolders and larger directory trees.

Version 2.0 introduces a Workbench 3.2 ReAction GUI and adds
DefIcons-based icon creation for supported files that do not
already have icons. It can also generate preview icons for
supported image and ASCII text files. Optional LhA-based backups
allow runs to be rolled back later if needed.

Main features include:
- Automatic icon grid layout
- Drawer window resizing and positioning
- Recursive processing of subfolders
- Optional LhA-based backup and restore
- Default Tool validation and repair
- Icon creation for selected file types using DefIcons
- Generated preview icons for supported image and ASCII text files

Usage:
Start iTidy from Workbench, select a folder or partition, choose
your options, and start processing. Recursive mode can be used to
tidy entire directory trees in one pass.

Notes:
- Processing large folder trees can take time on real hardware.
- Workbench may cache drawer window sizes until windows are reopened
  or Workbench is restarted.
- Layout backups and Default Tool backups are handled separately.

Documentation:
Full documentation is supplied in AmigaGuide format.
See iTidy2.guide for detailed usage instructions and option
descriptions.

Disclaimer:
This program is provided as-is and without warranty.
No responsibility is accepted for data loss or other damage.

Always back up important data before use.

CHANGELOG:
[2.0.0] - 2026-03-06
- New ReAction-based GUI for Workbench 3.2 and later
- Adds DefIcons integration for creating missing icons
- Adds generated preview icons for supported image and 
  ASCII text files
- Adds backup and restore support for layout changes
- Adds Default Tool validation and repair